The Red Scare, tinted lavender.At the height of the McCarthy era, naive college graduate Timothy Laughlin comes to Washington eager to join the crusade against communism. But a chance encounter with a handsome State Department official, Hawkins Fuller, leads to Tim‚Äôs first job‚Äîand his first relationship with a man.Under the threat of increased government scrutiny, this complicated and clandestine affair will put both men‚Äôs loyalties and convictions to the ultimate test. As the poisonous political climate pollutes their relationship, love becomes a casualty of what it takes to ‚Äúplay the game‚Äù in Washington.Based on Thomas Mallon‚Äôs 2007 gut-wrenching novel, Fellow Travelers was praised as ‚Äúa near-perfect example of fast-flowing musical drama‚Äù by The New York Times and is already widely considered a contemporary classic.

